Exercise 11.21: Assuming word_count is a map from string to size_t
and word is a string, explain the following loop:

while (cin >> word)
++word_count.insert({word, 0}).first->second;

Answer:
First create a pair from word and 0 then derefrence the the first value of the pair <iterator,bool> that is returned
by insert and increment the second value in the pair<string,size_t> of that word.